<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="way of life">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Way of Life.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Macrohabitat:</emphasis>
Lowlands, sea level, in the intertidal zone of beaches. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Microhabitat:</emphasis>
Adults are ground-dwelling on saline soils. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Dispersal abilities:</emphasis>
Macropterous, capable of flight; slow runners. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Seasonal occurrence:</emphasis>
Adults have been found in March and August. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Behavior:</emphasis>
Nocturnal predators, adults are attracted to lights.
</paragraph>
